recommandationVideos.Title: How to succeed the seedlings
recommandationVideos.Description:
For seedling success, do you need special compost created especially for seeds to germinate? Often not! 

In this new video, I show how to make your own seed compost, and how it's needed only for small seeds. 

For little seeds, ensure good drainage by adding up to 50% vermiculite or perlite, to your normal multipurpose/potting compost.
For most seeds including onions and brassicas, you can use 100% potting / multipurpose compost.

Germination and growth are stronger when you use decent trays. Preferably module trays, for better drainage than non-partitioned seed trays. I designed my CD trays to facilitate drainage and root-air. 
The small and tapering cells with a large bottom hole do not waterlog. So you can use normal potting compost for germinating most seeds. The polypropylene has a shiny smooth surface that helps plant rootballs to slide upwards. When sliding plants out, there is little or no damage to the roots, and none to the tray which is solid and made to last. 

Find more information in these YouTube videos:
https://youtu.be/GmWsM7odmkE
https://youtu.be/gK-Gkp_LTPc

My 60 cell and long life module trays are available in three sizes ‚Äì 15, 30 and 60 cell. Cell size is the same in all of these trays. The only variable is number of cells per tray.

Lt Gen Raghu Srinivasan, the Director General of the Border Roads Organisation (BRO) says of the critical road connectivity being built up in Eastern Ladakh and Siachen in the backdrop of the two-front threat from China and Pakistan. In this exclusive interview with¬†StratNews Global's¬†Amitabh P. Revi¬†on the frozen Zanskar River 'Chadar' Trail at Chiling near Leh in Ladakh, the DG notes "The impetus has over the last five or six years been a surge in what we are planning to do and are doing in Ladakh. The amount of projects which are being planned at the National and the Union Territory levels, the amount of funding, which is provided, and the way that projects are being cleared, all of it is phenomenal. We've not seen anything like it." Watch the complete interview with¬†Lt Gen Raghu Srinivasan,¬†the DG of the BRO in our series, 'The Himalayan Frontier'. Part V.

On the differences in road infrastructure in China-occupied Tibet and across the LAC, Lt Gen Srinivasan points out, "the Tibetan Plateau is at a lower altitude-between 12000 to 14000 feet. And it's a flat tabletop. There are no mountain ranges. So, whatever you're constructing is on a flat piece of ground. That's number one. Number two, the mountains are the watershed. That means whatever snow or moisture is going to come is going to stop in our portion. Tibet really is a flat, barren, cold desert. For anyone who constructs roads, moisture or water is a great enemy. That's what we need to work on. And see that we have ways by which we have adequate drainage. So whatever roads we construct are not washed away. Then starting from the south, you have the great Himalayan range, the Ladakh Range, and the Karakoram. There are a series of ranges. We have a very fragile mountain base. They are young mountains in terms of the Himalayas, and these are landslide-prone. With moisture, they become avalanche-prone and naturally you keep ascending, and you keep gaining height and then keep descending and losing height. So, the zig-zags that we have in each of these is essentially to get over a series of mountain ranges, which we have over an expanse of Ladakh, which is approximately 60,000 square kilometres".

SNG's team of¬†Amitabh P. Revi,¬†Rohit Pandita,¬†and¬†Karan Marwaha¬†documented their journey to Leh on the strategic third, alternate axis‚Äîthe Darcha-Padam-Nimu (NPD) Road, in¬†episode III¬†and¬†episode IV. The route provides critical connectivity for defence logistics to and civilian
development around the Northern China-occupied Tibet border or Line of Actual Control (LAC), the Line of Control (LoC), and the Actual Ground Position Line (AGPL) in Siachen with Pakistan. It is shielded from both the India-China border and the frontier with Pakistan, unlike the other two axes. StratNews Global's team travels during the fourth winter of India's forward deployment post Xi Jinping's aggression that led to the deadly Galwan clashes in 2020. The freezing temperatures highlight one of the several challenges the BRO faces in recce-ing, tracing, drilling through the mighty ranges, and building black-top roads on this route. India's infrastructure development has seen a sustained thrust, especially after China's People's Liberation Army (PLA) salami-slicing tactics in border areas.

recommandationVideos.Title: #China, #pakistan #ladakh Front: Roads Are Like Trees. Plant One & A Forest Develops: DG, BRO
recommandationVideos.Description:
Chiling, Ladakh:¬†"Making a road is a measure of a nation's sovereignty. It exercises command and control, and it says that these are my people". Lt Gen Raghu Srinivasan, the Director General of the Border Roads Organisation (BRO) says of the critical road connectivity being built up in Eastern Ladakh and Siachen in the backdrop of the two-front threat from China and Pakistan. In this exclusive interview with¬†StratNews Global's¬†Amitabh P. Revi¬†on the frozen Zanskar River 'Chadar' Trail at Chiling near Leh in Ladakh, the DG notes "The impetus has over the last five or six years been a surge in what we are planning to do and are doing in Ladakh. The amount of projects which are being planned at the National and the Union Territory levels, the amount of funding, which is provided, and the way that projects are being cleared, all of it is phenomenal. We've not seen anything like it." Watch the complete interview with¬†Lt Gen Raghu Srinivasan,¬†the DG of the BRO in our series, 'The Himalayan Frontier'. Part V.

On the differences in road infrastructure in China-occupied Tibet and across the LAC, Lt Gen Srinivasan points out, "the Tibetan Plateau is at a lower altitude-between 12000 to 14000 feet. And it's a flat tabletop. There are no mountain ranges. So, whatever you're constructing is on a flat piece of ground. That's number one. Number two, the mountains are the watershed. That means whatever snow or moisture is going to come is going to stop in our portion. Tibet really is a flat, barren, cold desert. For anyone who constructs roads, moisture or water is a great enemy. That's what we need to work on. And see that we have ways by which we have adequate drainage. So whatever roads we construct are not washed away. Then starting from the south, you have the great Himalayan range, the Ladakh Range, and the Karakoram. There are a series of ranges. We have a very fragile mountain base. They are young mountains in terms of the Himalayas, and these are landslide-prone. With moisture, they become avalanche-prone and naturally you keep ascending, and you keep gaining height and then keep descending and losing height. So, the zig-zags that we have in each of these is essentially to get over a series of mountain ranges, which we have over an expanse of Ladakh, which is approximately 60,000 square kilometres".

SNG's team of¬†Amitabh P. Revi,¬†Rohit Pandita,¬†and¬†Karan Marwaha¬†documented their journey to Leh on the strategic third, alternate axis‚Äîthe Darcha-Padam-Nimu (NPD) Road, in¬†episode III¬†and¬†episode IV. The route provides critical connectivity for defence logistics to and civilian
development around the Northern China-occupied Tibet border or Line of Actual Control (LAC), the Line of Control (LoC), and the Actual Ground Position Line (AGPL) in Siachen with Pakistan. It is shielded from both the India-China border and the frontier with Pakistan, unlike the other two axes. StratNews Global's team travels during the fourth winter of India's forward deployment post Xi Jinping's aggression that led to the deadly Galwan clashes in 2020. The freezing temperatures highlight one of the several challenges the BRO faces in recce-ing, tracing, drilling through the mighty ranges, and building black-top roads on this route. India's infrastructure development has seen a sustained thrust, especially after China's People's Liberation Army (PLA) salami-slicing tactics in border areas.

Erityisesti opposition puheenvuoroissaan nostamiin seikkoihin keskityn varmasti enemm√§n sitten debattipuheenvuoroissa, mutta nyt t√§h√§n valiokunnan mietint√∂√∂n. 

Vuoden 2024 talousarvioehdotus on 11,4 miljardia euroa alij√§√§m√§inen, ja valtion lopullinen nettolainanottotarve ylitt√§nee 10 miljardia euroa. Tilanne on julkisen talouden n√§k√∂kulmasta vakava. Julkisen velan kasvu on vaarallisen nousevalla uralla. Hallitus jatkaa m√§√§r√§tietoisesti entist√§ ajankohtaisemman hallitusohjelmansa toteuttamista. 

Valiokunta kiinnitt√§√§ mietinn√∂ss√§√§n huomiota moniin samoihin seikkoihin kuin mekin. Valtiovarainministeri√∂n syksyn taloudellisessa katsauksessa arvioitiin, ett√§ julkisen talouden alij√§√§m√§ on 2,4 prosenttia suhteessa bkt:hen vuonna 2023. Hallituksen p√§√§tt√§mist√§ sopeutustoimista huolimatta alij√§√§m√§ kasvaa yli kolmen prosentin vuonna 2024 ja edelleen noin 3,4 prosenttiin vuonna 2025. Talouden n√§kym√§t ovat kovin ep√§varmat. Uusi ennuste valmistuu ensi viikolla, eik√§ se tule n√§ytt√§m√§√§n parempaa vaan huonompaa. 

Julkisen talouden velkasuhde on ensi vuonna l√§hes 77 prosenttia. Taakka on kasvanut vuosikausia, samaan aikaan kun muut Pohjoismaat menev√§t toiseen suuntaan. Valtion, hyvinvointialueiden ja kuntien yhteenlaskettu mittava alij√§√§m√§, v√§est√∂n ik√§√§ntyminen sek√§ kasvavat velanhoitokustannukset pit√§v√§t velkasuhteen nousevalla uralla my√∂s jatkossa. Talouden kuva on utuinen, ja tulevaan kasvuun ja verotuloarvioon liittyy merkitt√§v√§ m√§√§r√§ ep√§varmuutta. Geopoliittinen tilanne ei helpota tilannekuvan muodostamista. On varauduttava ik√§viin yll√§tyksiin ja riskien realisoitumiseen. En voi liiaksi korostaa, vaikka kuulostan hyvin pessimistiselt√§, miten vakava tilanne on. Poliittisilta p√§√§t√∂ksentekij√∂ilt√§ vaaditaan m√§√§r√§tietoisuutta, rohkeutta ja selk√§rankaa. 

Arvoisa puhemies! Tilannekuva vahvistaa sit√§ k√§sityst√§, ett√§ hallituksen talouspoliittinen strategia on oikea ja tarpeellinen. Palaamme noudattamaan kurinalaista budjettipolitiikkaa. Palaamme tiukkaan kehysmenettelyyn, josta edellinen hallitus lipsui ja lopulta luopui. Kehysmenettely pit√§√§ meid√§t poliitikot kurissa ja tarjoaa kuluttajansuojaa √§√§nest√§j√§lle ja veronmaksajalle. Meill√§ ei ole varaa en√§√§ kalliiseen intressiryhm√§talouspolitiikkaan. 

Kehystaso nousee vaalikauden keskivaiheilla, ja t√§m√§ johtuu siit√§, ett√§ joudumme valitettavasti varautumaan edellisen hallituksen luomaan menopaineeseen sote-uudistuksesta. Hyvinvointialueiden talous on [Annika Saarikon v√§lihuuto] huonossa kunnossa, ja varsinkin kalliit ostopalvelut viev√§t alueiden talouden rankasti alij√§√§m√§iseksi jo kuluvana vuonna, arvioiden mukaan jopa 1,3 miljardia euroa, pahimmassa tapauksessa enemm√§n. Aika n√§ytt√§√§, mik√§ on alueiden elinkelpoisuus. Hallitusohjelmassa on joitakin kirjauksia siit√§, miten alueiden taloudenpitoa saadaan parannettua, mutta nykytilanteen valossa n√§kym√§ on t√§√§ll√§kin synkk√§. Hyvinvointialueiden paisuvat menot on pakko saada kuriin, [Annika Saarikon v√§lihuuto] koska ik√§√§ntyminen joka tapauksessa takaa rahantarpeen kasvun. 

Sotealueiden alij√§√§m√§t t√§lt√§ vuodelta aiheuttavat merkitt√§v√§n menoer√§n valtiolle vuonna 2025, kun rahoitus tarkistetaan ensimm√§isen kerran. Kehysvarauksen tarjoama liikkumatila pienenee edelleen vaalikauden loppua kohti. 

Samoin kuntien peruspalvelujen valtionosuuksien mahdollinen kompensointi aiheuttaa paineita valtiontalouteen, erityisesti vuodesta 2025 alkaen. Valtion budjettitalouden n√§k√∂kulmasta kompensointi tuottaa lis√§s√§√§st√∂tarpeita, jotta kompensointi olisi koko julkisen talouden tasolla neutraali. Lis√§s√§√§st√∂jen tarve vuodelle 2025 on t√§ll√§ hetkell√§ 500 miljoonasta eurosta miljardiin ‚Äî t√§ll√§ hetkell√§. Samaan aikaan esimerkiksi komissio on huomauttanut jo ensi vuoden selv√§sti liikaa kasvavista menoistamme. Suomella on merkitt√§vi√§ haasteita valtiontalouden sopeuttamisessa. 

Arvoisa puhemies! Valiokunta kiinnitt√§√§ huomiota valtion korkoriskeihin. Muutamia vuosia sitten keskuspankit painoivat yleisen korkotason nollaan tai sen alle. My√∂s pitk√§t valtionlainojen korot painuivat nollaan rahapolitiikan tuolloisen virityksen vuoksi. Korkolasku tulikin siit√§ huolimatta maksettavaksi, ja hallituksen talousarvioehdotuksessa ensi vuodelle korkoihin budjetoidaan yli kolme miljardia euroa. T√§m√§ on pois kaikesta hyv√§st√§, kuten koulutuksesta, terveydenhuollosta ja turvallisuudesta. Velan kasvavat korkokulut ja krooniset alij√§√§m√§t johtavat yhdess√§ ep√§edulliseen velkadynamiikkaan ja velkasuhteen kasvuun. 

My√∂s valtion taseen ulkopuoliset vastuut, kuten takaukset, ovat kasvussa. N√§ist√§kin osa voi realisoitua valtion menoina. Valiokunta kiinnitt√§√§ mietinn√∂ss√§√§n t√§h√§nkin aiheellista huomiota.

T√§m√§ tapa... [V√§lihuutoja vasemmalta] ‚Äî Totta kai se on totta, mutta jos te... [H√§lin√§√§ ‚Äî Puhemies koputtaa] T√§ss√§k√∂ on opposition laatu? Kyll√§ olen eritt√§in huolestunut, mutta minua ei yll√§t√§ lainkaan, ett√§ vuodesta 2008 me olemme sit√§ velkaa kasvattaneet ja tehneet alij√§√§m√§isi√§ budjetteja, mik√§li teid√§n taloudellinen osaamisenne on n√§in heikkoa. Pelk√§st√§√§n korkoihin menee ensi vuonna 3,2 miljardia euroa. Muistelen t√§√§lt√§ salista: aivan hetki sitten te viel√§ kerroitte, ett√§ valtionvelalla ei edes ole merkityst√§ ja sit√§ ei v√§ltt√§m√§tt√§ tarvitse edes maksaa takaisin. [V√§lihuutoja vasemmalta] T√§m√§ on kerta kaikkisen ep√§rehellist√§. T√§m√§ on poliittista populismia pahimmillaan, mihin te t√§ll√§ hetkell√§ syyllistytte. [Jussi Saramo: Ministeri ei puhu totta!]  

Samaan aikaan, arvoisa puhemies, t√§√§ll√§ sosiaalidemokraatit sanoivat, ett√§ me teemme, hetkinen, ‚Äùhistoriallisen suuret leikkaukset‚Äù, vasemmisto k√§ytti termi√§ ‚Äùennenn√§kem√§tt√∂m√§n suuret leikkaukset‚Äù. [Kimmo Kiljunen: T√§ll√§ vuosituhannella!] Me teemme 800 miljoonan nettomenos√§√§st√∂t ensi vuodelle, kun budjetin loppusumma on l√§hes 80 miljardia. Se, ett√§ teille eiv√§t kelpaa meid√§n toimenpiteemme, te puututte mieluummin olutveroon tai solidaarisuusveroon, on teid√§n valintanne, [Kimmo Kiljunen: Arvovalintoja!] mutta kuten olen aiemminkin sanonut, niin jos valtion budjettia ei kykene tarkastelemaan kokonaisuudessaan eli sen ylivoimaisesti suurimpia osa-alueita ‚Äî kyll√§, k√§yt√§n my√∂s sit√§ termi√§ ‚Äùsosiaalivaltio‚Äù, koska se on niin paisunut ‚Äî niin te ette valitettavasti p√§√§se niihin tavoitteisiin, joita t√§m√§n julkisen talouden korjaaminen, valtion budjettitalouden korjaaminen ja kehyksiss√§ pysyminen vaativat. Arvoisa puhemies! recommandationVideos.Title: E361 Navigating the Bible: The Pentateuch
recommandationVideos.Description:
Join Saddleback Church's Doable Discipleship podcast in a series on Navigating the Bible. Have you ever wondered how to read the Bible? What do you need to know about different sections of the Bible that would help you read it better? This series seeks to give you a primer on the different major sections of the Bible. Each week, host Jason Wieland is joined by a different Bible expert to talk through the major details, authors, cultural context, and other important information on the major sections of the Bible. 

This episode focus in on the Pentateuch. Jason is joined by Dr. Charlie Trimm, associate professor and chair of Old Testament at Biola University. The conversation looks at the themes found in the Pentateuch, when they were written, the cultural context, what you should know about Moses, and much more. 

Doable Discipleship is a Saddleback Church podcast produced and hosted by the Saddleback Spiritual Growth Team. It premiered in 2017 and now offers more than 350 episodes. Episodes release every Tuesday on your favorite podcast app and on the Saddleback Church YouTube Channel (https://www.youtube.com/saddleback). 

Doable Discipleship is a proud part of the Saddleback Family of Podcasts. To learn more about the Saddleback Family of Podcasts, visit saddleback.com/podcasts.
